WEBVTT

00:11.745 --> 00:14.647
[insects chirping]

00:14.714 --> 00:17.851
[distant siren wailing]

00:34.667 --> 00:37.570
[siren wailing]

00:37.670 --> 00:40.740
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:22.749 --> 01:25.885
<i>- [sobbing loudly]</i>

01:29.956 --> 01:35.895
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:46.940 --> 01:50.677
[monitor beeping]

01:50.777 --> 01:52.779
[elevator bell dings]

01:52.846 --> 01:56.749
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:56.816 --> 01:59.285
- This room
is a personal favorite of mine.

01:59.352 --> 02:01.454
Everything in here is original,

02:01.521 --> 02:03.590
preserved in time.

02:03.656 --> 02:08.027
You'll be joining some
very distinguished company.

02:08.127 --> 02:09.496
- I bet.

02:09.596 --> 02:13.666
- Some of the first guests
at the Riverview were

02:13.766 --> 02:16.436
<i>numerous celebrities</i>

02:16.503 --> 02:19.139
<i>and movie stars.</i>

02:20.507 --> 02:21.875
<i>- Like who?</i>

02:21.975 --> 02:25.445
<i>I'm not at liberty</i>
<i>to divulge their names,</i>

02:25.512 --> 02:27.347
<i>but rest assured,</i>

02:27.447 --> 02:30.884
the names would impress you.

02:30.984 --> 02:33.153
- I'm sure.

02:34.554 --> 02:37.557
Thank you
for the history lesson.

02:37.657 --> 02:40.026
<i>- You're welcome.</i>

02:42.629 --> 02:44.631
<i>- Actress Brittany Murphy,</i>

02:44.697 --> 02:46.799
<i>who began her career</i>
<i>in the early 1990s</i>

02:46.866 --> 02:48.735
<i>and became well-known</i>
<i>for her roles</i>

02:48.835 --> 02:52.038
<i>in "Girl, Interrupted,"</i>
<i>"Clueless," and "8 Mile,"</i>

02:52.138 --> 02:53.840
<i>has died at the age of 32.</i>

02:53.907 --> 02:56.743
<i>She was pronounced dead</i>
<i>at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center</i>

02:56.843 --> 02:58.378
<i>just after 10:00 a.m.</i>

02:58.478 --> 03:05.552
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:12.825 --> 03:15.495
<i>- ♪ I had it all planned out ♪</i>

03:15.562 --> 03:18.331
<i>♪ Before you met me ♪</i>

03:18.398 --> 03:20.867
<i>♪ Was gonna leave early ♪</i>

03:20.934 --> 03:23.069
<i>♪ So swiftly ♪</i>

03:23.169 --> 03:27.740
<i>♪ Maybe in a fire</i>
<i>or crash off a ravine ♪</i>

03:27.840 --> 03:29.409
<i>♪ People would weep ♪</i>

03:29.509 --> 03:32.912
<i>♪ How tragic, so early ♪</i>

03:33.012 --> 03:37.450
<i>♪ I was gonna die young ♪</i>

03:37.550 --> 03:42.422
<i>♪ Now I gotta wait</i>
<i>for you, honey ♪</i>

03:42.522 --> 03:47.227
<i>♪ I was gonna</i>
<i>die young ♪</i>

03:49.362 --> 03:52.031
- Take three, mark.

03:52.098 --> 03:53.533
- Thank you.

03:53.600 --> 03:54.767
<i>Good? Okay.</i>

03:54.867 --> 03:56.436
Here's something
I just want to say,

03:56.536 --> 03:59.205
'cause I want
to make sure we get it in.

03:59.272 --> 04:01.474
I know people always say,
"I don't want blah, blah,

04:01.574 --> 04:04.043
remembered for blah, blah,
what happened to them."

04:04.110 --> 04:07.046
But, like, all of us agree

04:07.113 --> 04:10.817
that one of the most
painful things about this,

04:10.917 --> 04:13.286
other than losing a life
way too soon

04:13.386 --> 04:17.257
and for such
egregiously wrong reasons,

04:17.323 --> 04:21.928
is that
Brittany was so wonderful.

04:21.995 --> 04:24.397
Like, there was
nobody else like her.

04:26.799 --> 04:29.302
<i>She wasn't a Hollywood girl.</i>

04:29.402 --> 04:32.438
The movie of her life is like--
who walks into a room

04:32.505 --> 04:34.140
<i>and almost every</i>
<i>single person there</i>

04:34.240 --> 04:36.976
<i>is thrilled that you're there</i>
<i>and then knows</i>

04:37.076 --> 04:39.679
<i>that when she leaves the room</i>
<i>and goes home,</i>

04:39.779 --> 04:43.082
<i>she's the same freaking person</i>

04:43.149 --> 04:45.652
<i>in the movie of her life?</i>

04:45.752 --> 04:49.022
<i>[light music]</i>

04:49.122 --> 04:50.857
<i>- It's weird</i>
<i>'cause stuff happens,</i>

04:50.957 --> 04:52.959
<i>and you don't really notice it</i>
<i>while it's happening.</i>

04:53.026 --> 04:54.927
Life is sort of passing by.

04:56.362 --> 04:58.131
[siren wailing]

04:58.197 --> 05:02.001
<i>[indistinct chatter</i>
<i>over police radio]</i>

05:02.101 --> 05:03.670
<i>- Media and paparazzi</i>

05:03.770 --> 05:06.105
<i>surrounded Brittany Murphy's</i>
<i>Hollywood Hills home</i>

05:06.172 --> 05:08.341
<i>that she shared with her</i>
<i>husband of nearly three years,</i>

05:08.441 --> 05:10.677
<i>British screenwriter</i>
<i>Simon Monjack.</i>

05:10.777 --> 05:12.312
<i>The world is stunned</i>
<i>by the loss</i>

05:12.378 --> 05:16.049
<i>of the seemingly healthy,</i>
<i>young actress.</i>

05:16.149 --> 05:17.517
- I got a call from my editor.

05:17.617 --> 05:19.185
He said,
"Brittany Murphy's died.

05:19.285 --> 05:21.187
"Get over to her house
immediately."

05:21.287 --> 05:23.022
You know, "Get the scoop."

05:23.122 --> 05:25.191
<i>When I got there,</i>
<i>I can remember, like, barely</i>

05:25.291 --> 05:26.893
<i>having anywhere</i>
<i>to park my car</i>

05:26.993 --> 05:29.862
<i>because there were so many</i>
<i>reporters and paparazzi</i>

05:29.962 --> 05:32.198
<i>all just at the foot</i>
<i>of her driveway,</i>

05:32.298 --> 05:35.301
<i>waiting, hoping that maybe</i>
<i>her husband would come out.</i>

05:35.368 --> 05:37.403
<i>[camera shutter clicks]</i>

05:37.503 --> 05:40.707
<i>I'd never heard of him</i>
<i>before he married Brittany</i>

05:40.807 --> 05:42.709
<i>and barely even after</i>
<i>he married Brittany.</i>

05:42.809 --> 05:44.243
They weren't
the Hollywood couple

05:44.344 --> 05:46.713
that was photographed out
at dinner all the time.

05:46.813 --> 05:48.181
They were never out.

05:48.247 --> 05:50.383
<i>He was mysterious</i>
<i>in the way of, like,</i>

05:50.483 --> 05:51.751
<i>"Who are you?"</i>

05:51.851 --> 05:53.052
<i>But we didn't know</i>
<i>what happened.</i>

05:53.152 --> 05:55.655
<i>All we knew is that this young</i>

05:55.722 --> 05:57.490
<i>32-year-old Hollywood starlet</i>

05:57.557 --> 05:59.392
<i>had suddenly died.</i>

05:59.492 --> 06:00.993
<i>- It came across my newsfeed--</i>

06:01.060 --> 06:02.895
<i>"Brittany Murphy dies</i>
<i>at 32 years old."</i>

06:02.995 --> 06:04.897
And I was like, "What?"

06:04.997 --> 06:07.266
- Today I'm going to be
telling you guys

06:07.367 --> 06:08.534
about a true crime story

06:08.601 --> 06:10.236
that I am really interested in,

06:10.336 --> 06:12.071
as well as doing my makeup.

06:12.171 --> 06:14.574
- Could have Brittany Murphy's
death been prevented?

06:14.674 --> 06:16.008
Absolutely.

06:16.075 --> 06:20.179
- She was dealing
with an eating disorder.

06:20.246 --> 06:22.915
- Everybody thought, like,
"Did she overdose?"

06:23.015 --> 06:25.918
<i>- This shady business guy</i>
<i>that Brittany married,</i>

06:26.018 --> 06:27.687
something freaky happened.

06:27.754 --> 06:30.623
- [whispering] That could mean
that she was being poisoned.

06:30.723 --> 06:33.359
<i>- The FBI was watching them.</i>

06:33.426 --> 06:34.627
- Is the house cursed?

06:34.727 --> 06:37.764
- I called it.
I knew she was murdered.

06:37.864 --> 06:40.933
<i>- Brittany Murphy--</i>
<i>what could have happened?</i>

06:41.033 --> 06:43.269
<i>- Speculation's mounting</i>
<i>about the sudden death</i>

06:43.369 --> 06:45.204
<i>of actress Brittany Murphy.</i>

06:45.271 --> 06:47.640
<i>Ed Winter is</i>
<i>the assistant chief coroner.</i>

06:47.740 --> 06:49.308
- We're conducting
an investigation

06:49.409 --> 06:51.444
into the death
of Brittany Murphy.

06:54.046 --> 06:55.615
<i>My name is Ed Winter.</i>

06:55.715 --> 06:58.651
I oversaw the high-profile
celebrity deaths,

06:58.751 --> 07:01.621
including Brittany Murphy's.

07:01.721 --> 07:05.458
<i>We responded to the residence,</i>
<i>to her next of kin,</i>

07:05.558 --> 07:09.495
<i>her husband, Simon,</i>
<i>and Brittany's mother, Sharon.</i>

07:09.595 --> 07:11.597
<i>Sharon was sitting</i>
<i>on the couch,</i>

07:11.664 --> 07:13.566
<i>and she'd cry a little bit,</i>
<i>and then she'd stop,</i>

07:13.633 --> 07:15.802
<i>and she'd talk with Simon</i>
<i>or say something</i>

07:15.902 --> 07:18.638
and then start crying again.

07:18.738 --> 07:22.074
<i>Simon appeared to be</i>
<i>somewhat under the influence,</i>

07:22.141 --> 07:23.476
<i>just pacing around,</i>

07:23.576 --> 07:25.411
<i>and he maybe</i>
<i>wasn't totally coherent.</i>

07:25.478 --> 07:27.113
There were several
little indicators

07:27.180 --> 07:29.081
that just didn't feel right,
you know?

07:29.148 --> 07:32.652
You get that--the hair on the
back of your neck stands up,

07:32.752 --> 07:34.620
and it's like, "What?"

07:34.687 --> 07:36.923
<i>[eerie music]</i>

07:36.989 --> 07:39.759
<i>They basically said</i>
<i>that they were up late.</i>

07:39.826 --> 07:41.594
<i>She had flu-like symptoms.</i>

07:41.661 --> 07:45.097
<i>They'd been in Puerto Rico</i>
<i>two weeks earlier.</i>

07:45.164 --> 07:49.302
<i>And when they were there,</i>
<i>she became ill.</i>

07:49.368 --> 07:52.472
<i>In the morning,</i>
<i>Brittany went in the bathroom,</i>

07:52.538 --> 07:54.040
<i>and after a short time,</i>

07:54.140 --> 07:56.309
<i>Sharon discovered her</i>
<i>unresponsive</i>

07:56.375 --> 07:58.644
<i>on the bathroom floor.</i>

07:58.711 --> 08:01.814
<i>They carried her</i>
<i>into the shower</i>

08:01.881 --> 08:03.516
<i>and turned on cold water</i>

08:03.616 --> 08:05.551
<i>to see if they could</i>
<i>revive her.</i>

08:05.651 --> 08:08.354
<i>There was a delay</i>
<i>to start CPR.</i>

08:08.454 --> 08:11.023
<i>What's going on?</i>
<i>Why did it get that far?</i>

08:11.123 --> 08:13.059
<i>And if she's sick,</i>
<i>why didn't somebody</i>

08:13.159 --> 08:15.828
pick up the phone
or make arrangements?

08:15.895 --> 08:18.197
Come on,
something isn't right.

08:18.297 --> 08:20.166
<i>We'll be doing an autopsy.</i>

08:20.233 --> 08:22.201
The final results will be

08:22.301 --> 08:25.538
pending toxicology
and further tests.

08:27.206 --> 08:30.076
- The chatter among us
was overdose.

08:30.176 --> 08:33.212
I mean, it seemed like
the only logical thing

08:33.312 --> 08:35.748
for someone that young
in Hollywood.

08:35.848 --> 08:39.886
<i>Brittany had changed</i>
<i>physically noticeably.</i>

08:39.986 --> 08:41.420
<i>She was much thinner.</i>

08:41.520 --> 08:44.323
We thought,
"Well, she went too far."

08:44.390 --> 08:45.558
[car horn blares]

08:45.658 --> 08:49.762
- I kind of fucked it up.
[sighs]

08:49.862 --> 08:52.732
[whooshing]

09:02.542 --> 09:03.576
<i>- Good afternoon, everybody.</i>

09:03.676 --> 09:05.211
<i>My name is Ryk Schoonhiem,</i>

09:05.278 --> 09:06.946
<i>and here we are</i>
<i>at the 27th annual</i>

09:07.046 --> 09:08.681
Metuchen Country Fair.

09:08.748 --> 09:11.784
This is "Metuchen on the Air."

09:11.884 --> 09:13.352
Excuse me?
- Would you like a children's--

09:13.419 --> 09:14.720
- Yes, I would like
a children's perspective.

09:14.787 --> 09:15.922
- Great.

09:16.022 --> 09:17.256
- What is your name?
- Brittany.

09:17.356 --> 09:18.624
- Brittany, how you doing
today, Brittany?

09:18.724 --> 09:20.092
- Great, how are you?
- Very good.

09:20.192 --> 09:21.427
You want a job hosting
a television show?

09:21.527 --> 09:22.895
- Sure.
- How about you interview

09:22.962 --> 09:25.698
these people over here?
- Okay, sure.

09:25.765 --> 09:27.867
Hi, do you like
the fair here today?

09:27.934 --> 09:29.368
- Yeah.
- What's your name?

09:29.435 --> 09:30.536
- Carissa.

09:30.603 --> 09:32.071
- Where are you from?
- Edison.

09:32.138 --> 09:33.739
- You're from Edison.
Oh, my goodness.

09:33.806 --> 09:35.274
How old are you?
- 11.

09:35.374 --> 09:37.944
- Why are you here
at the fair today?

09:38.044 --> 09:38.945
- 'Cause it's fun.

09:39.045 --> 09:41.080
- Nice talking with you.

09:41.147 --> 09:43.149
- Give us your name,
and what school do you go to?

09:43.249 --> 09:45.618
- [laughs]
Hi, my name is Brittany Murphy,

09:45.718 --> 09:47.787
and I go to
Herbert Hoover Middle School.

09:47.887 --> 09:49.555
[giggles]

09:49.622 --> 09:51.424
Thank you.

09:51.490 --> 09:53.993
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:54.093 --> 09:55.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:55.995 --> 09:58.631
We're gonna be friends.

09:58.731 --> 10:00.833
Okay?

10:00.933 --> 10:03.603
- Grown-ups never stay friends
with kids.

10:05.571 --> 10:09.275
- I don't see
any grown-ups around here.

10:10.910 --> 10:12.778
<i>- You raised her</i>
<i>as a single mom?</i>

10:12.845 --> 10:13.846
<i>- Yes, yeah.</i>

10:13.946 --> 10:15.815
<i>- What happened to her dad?</i>

10:15.915 --> 10:18.517
<i>- He was never around.</i>
<i>It was just us.</i>

10:18.618 --> 10:20.119
<i>- So she had no father</i>
<i>growing up?</i>

10:20.186 --> 10:21.654
<i>- No, not at all.</i>

10:21.754 --> 10:23.623
<i>- Did she always</i>
<i>want to be in show business?</i>

10:23.689 --> 10:25.257
<i>- Yes, she started, you know,</i>

10:25.324 --> 10:27.827
<i>in dance school and</i>
<i>musical comedy classes</i>

10:27.927 --> 10:29.362
<i>when she was little</i>

10:29.462 --> 10:31.530
<i>because she always had</i>
<i>so much energy,</i>

10:31.631 --> 10:35.368
<i>and she just came out of me</i>
<i>a show person.</i>

10:35.468 --> 10:37.269
[indistinct shouting]

10:37.336 --> 10:40.940
- My name is Really Rosie!

10:41.007 --> 10:44.143
♪ I'm Really Rosie ♪

10:44.210 --> 10:46.545
- Well, I have
a bunch of photos

10:46.646 --> 10:49.448
of our production
of "Really Rosie."

10:49.515 --> 10:52.618
She was so spectacular
in this show.

10:52.685 --> 10:53.819
<i>My name is John Menter,</i>

10:53.886 --> 10:55.187
and I was Brittany Murphy's

10:55.287 --> 10:57.623
earliest acting coach/director.

10:57.690 --> 10:59.158
<i>We had an audition.</i>

10:59.225 --> 11:02.361
<i>In walked Sharon</i>
<i>and little Brittany Murphy.</i>

11:02.461 --> 11:04.664
They were an hour late,
maybe even more so.

11:04.730 --> 11:07.533
When she came in, you know,
"My name is Brittany Murphy,"

11:07.633 --> 11:10.870
and, you know,
she handed us the head shot.

11:10.970 --> 11:12.538
And they were like,
"Can we still audition?"

11:12.638 --> 11:14.707
We said, "Yeah, sure.
Go on, you know, audition."

11:14.807 --> 11:16.308
<i>So she sang her song,</i>

11:16.375 --> 11:19.812
and it's that look towards
the other people like,

11:19.879 --> 11:21.814
"We have someone
very rare here."

11:21.881 --> 11:23.549
<i>And the rest is history.</i>

11:23.649 --> 11:26.252
- How old are you?
- I'm ten years old.

11:27.486 --> 11:28.821
- Where's this all leading?

11:28.888 --> 11:31.891
- Broadway or Hollywood.
[laughs] Both.

11:31.991 --> 11:34.827
First, I wanted to get
into Broadway, then Hollywood.

11:34.894 --> 11:37.730
And then I just want to do
a bunch of things.

11:37.830 --> 11:41.200
<i>- This is a really cute</i>
<i>picture of Britt.</i>

11:41.267 --> 11:44.070
<i>She's waving to me.</i>

11:44.170 --> 11:45.271
- I'm Kelley Faulkner,

11:45.371 --> 11:47.239
and I met Brittany
when I was 11,

11:47.339 --> 11:49.909
<i>doing a play together</i>
<i>in New Jersey.</i>

11:50.009 --> 11:52.411
- And I'm Kelly's mom,
Marti Faulkner,

11:52.511 --> 11:56.282
<i>and Sharon and I became</i>
<i>very good friends.</i>

11:56.382 --> 11:58.184
<i>Lovely people.</i>

11:58.250 --> 12:00.286
I'm gonna tear up...
[inhales deeply]

12:00.386 --> 12:02.088
Because Brittany never said

12:02.188 --> 12:05.524
an unkind word
about anybody, ever.

12:05.591 --> 12:09.028
She was very funny,
really funny.

12:09.095 --> 12:11.097
She made me laugh a lot.

12:11.197 --> 12:14.133
<i>- We just really loved</i>
<i>each other fiercely.</i>

12:14.233 --> 12:17.203
<i>She had a really naturally</i>
<i>bright and bubbly personality,</i>

12:17.269 --> 12:19.638
<i>and it was completely genuine.</i>

12:19.739 --> 12:22.908
<i>One night, she got</i>
<i>to the second verse</i>

12:22.975 --> 12:26.145
and just completely blanked
and forgot the words.

12:26.245 --> 12:30.449
She launched into
a fully improvised dance break

12:30.549 --> 12:32.618
with high kicks and pirouettes

12:32.718 --> 12:34.420
and then just
finished the song.

12:34.487 --> 12:36.055
<i>It really summed up</i>

12:36.122 --> 12:37.823
<i>exactly who she was</i>
<i>as a performer,</i>

12:37.923 --> 12:41.160
which was fearless
and in the moment.

12:41.260 --> 12:42.795
<i>- A lot of people say,</i>
<i>"Oh, I bet you</i>

12:42.895 --> 12:44.563
her mother pushed her
into showbiz."

12:44.630 --> 12:46.065
And I would say,
"Absolutely not."

12:46.132 --> 12:47.933
<i>I really felt</i>
<i>that it was something</i>

12:48.000 --> 12:49.969
<i>that Brittany wanted to do.</i>

12:50.069 --> 12:53.639
<i>Brittany definitely maxed out</i>
<i>in New Jersey.</i>

12:53.739 --> 12:56.275
Sharon asked Brittany,
you know,

12:56.342 --> 12:58.944
"Is this something
you really want to pursue?"

12:59.011 --> 13:00.446
And Brittany said,
yes, she did,

13:00.513 --> 13:01.914
and then Sharon said, "Okay,

13:01.981 --> 13:04.316
"I'm gonna leave my job
here in New Jersey,

13:04.416 --> 13:06.786
and we're gonna
move to California."

13:06.852 --> 13:09.789
<i>[spacey music]</i>

13:09.855 --> 13:13.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:13.459 --> 13:14.960
<i>[bell tolls]</i>

13:15.027 --> 13:17.630
<i>- Family and friends</i>
<i>of actress Brittany Murphy</i>

13:17.696 --> 13:19.832
<i>arrived</i>
<i>at a Los Angeles cemetery</i>

13:19.932 --> 13:21.500
<i>for a private funeral.</i>

13:21.600 --> 13:23.636
<i>A friend who eulogized</i>
<i>the actress</i>

13:23.702 --> 13:25.271
<i>said Murphy loved Christmas</i>

13:25.337 --> 13:27.206
<i>and noted the irony</i>
<i>of her being buried</i>

13:27.306 --> 13:28.607
<i>on Christmas Eve.</i>

13:28.674 --> 13:31.210
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:31.310 --> 13:33.512
<i>- We scheduled the funeral</i>
<i>for a certain time</i>

13:33.612 --> 13:35.347
<i>so it would be over</i>
<i>and people wouldn't be</i>

13:35.447 --> 13:37.716
<i>walking around in the dark.</i>

13:37.817 --> 13:40.619
<i>But the lights of Burbank</i>

13:40.686 --> 13:42.822
<i>started just to twinkle</i>

13:42.888 --> 13:44.623
<i>ever so slightly,</i>

13:44.690 --> 13:47.359
<i>and day turned to night.</i>

13:47.459 --> 13:49.461
<i>There was a beauty to it.</i>

13:49.528 --> 13:53.132
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:53.199 --> 13:54.466
<i>- I'm Sara Hammel,</i>

13:54.533 --> 13:56.802
and I was working
in "People" magazine's

13:56.869 --> 13:59.905
Los Angeles bureau
when Brittany Murphy died.

14:00.005 --> 14:02.875
My job was to find out
what she'd been up to

14:02.975 --> 14:05.377
in her last days,
talk to people who knew her.

14:05.477 --> 14:07.379
What could have gone wrong?
What happened?

14:07.479 --> 14:09.181
You would hear
some different stories,

14:09.248 --> 14:12.718
but the one story
that remained consistent

14:12.818 --> 14:14.887
was that Simon Monjack
was bad for her.

14:14.987 --> 14:16.989
<i>[camera shutter clicking]</i>

14:17.056 --> 14:20.226
<i>She first met him in 2006.</i>

14:20.326 --> 14:23.395
<i>He was known as a writer.</i>

14:23.495 --> 14:25.164
He was always
in the background,

14:25.231 --> 14:27.066
and we were always sort of
interested in Brittany Murphy,

14:27.166 --> 14:28.701
<i>but once they got married,</i>

14:28.767 --> 14:32.538
<i>they were holed up</i>
<i>in that house 24-7.</i>

14:33.839 --> 14:36.342
<i>- So it was very interesting</i>
<i>when Simon Monjack</i>

14:36.408 --> 14:37.710
came on to the scene

14:37.776 --> 14:40.112
because nobody
was really aware of him

14:40.212 --> 14:42.414
until they were aware
of him, right?

14:42.514 --> 14:44.250
- Brittany, there's
a little kid back here that--

14:44.350 --> 14:45.918
- No.

14:46.018 --> 14:47.920
<i>- He seemed a lot older</i>
<i>than her.</i>

14:48.020 --> 14:50.022
<i>I don't want to use</i>
<i>the Svengali phrase,</i>

14:50.089 --> 14:53.025
but it seemed more like

14:53.092 --> 14:55.628
a control kind of issue.

14:55.728 --> 14:56.729
- Last one, guys.

14:56.795 --> 14:58.430
- All right.
- That's it.

14:58.530 --> 15:00.432
<i>- This was a marriage</i>
<i>between a fading starlet</i>

15:00.532 --> 15:02.067
<i>and an unknown screenwriter.</i>

15:02.134 --> 15:03.702
<i>- She was recently</i>
<i>married, right?</i>

15:03.769 --> 15:05.638
<i>- She was married</i>
<i>about three years ago.</i>

15:05.738 --> 15:07.273
<i>Yeah, Simon Monjack.</i>

15:07.373 --> 15:09.375
Now, the thing that's very
strange about him, though,

15:09.441 --> 15:12.945
is that he has said
he doesn't want an autopsy.

15:13.045 --> 15:16.582
<i>- Simon did request</i>
<i>that no autopsy be done.</i>

15:16.649 --> 15:18.584
And sometimes
that's an indicator

15:18.651 --> 15:21.787
that somebody
doesn't want you to find out

15:21.887 --> 15:23.656
<i>what they had in their system.</i>

15:23.756 --> 15:25.124
<i>And I explained to him,</i>

15:25.224 --> 15:26.992
<i>"There's going to be</i>
<i>an autopsy,</i>

15:27.092 --> 15:30.729
<i>and we need to find out</i>
<i>why she passed away."</i>

15:30.796 --> 15:33.232
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:33.299 --> 15:35.134
<i>- We were waiting</i>
<i>for the autopsy,</i>

15:35.234 --> 15:36.902
<i>and you start to think,</i>
<i>"Well, okay,</i>

15:36.969 --> 15:38.804
<i>who gained from her dying?"</i>

15:38.904 --> 15:40.739
<i>And then he's living</i>
<i>in this house</i>

15:40.806 --> 15:42.341
<i>with Brittany's mom's still.</i>

15:42.441 --> 15:43.976
<i>[camera shutter clicking]</i>

15:44.076 --> 15:45.577
<i>- There was a set of pictures</i>
<i>that came out</i>

15:45.644 --> 15:47.446
<i>taken by a photographer</i>
<i>friend of mine</i>

15:47.513 --> 15:49.448
<i>of Simon Monjack</i>
<i>with Sharon Murphy.</i>

15:49.515 --> 15:51.417
<i>It looked like</i>
<i>parents grieving,</i>

15:51.483 --> 15:54.486
<i>as opposed to a husband</i>
<i>and his mother-in-law.</i>

15:54.586 --> 15:56.155
But it was creepy.

15:56.255 --> 15:59.191
<i>- Him and Sharon still lived</i>
<i>in the house together.</i>

15:59.291 --> 16:01.760
So people suspected
that Simon

16:01.827 --> 16:04.296
<i>may have had something to do</i>

16:04.363 --> 16:06.198
<i>with Brittany's death.</i>

16:06.298 --> 16:08.867
- A 32-year-old woman

16:08.968 --> 16:10.970
passes away suddenly,

16:11.036 --> 16:13.005
and you don't want
an autopsy done?

16:13.105 --> 16:15.607
What is going on?

16:15.674 --> 16:21.647
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:21.714 --> 16:23.882
- The amount
of reporters and paparazzi

16:23.983 --> 16:25.484
sort of dwindled off,

16:25.551 --> 16:26.552
and we stayed.

16:26.652 --> 16:28.220
We were told to stay.

16:28.320 --> 16:30.155
<i>Spent the night in my car.</i>

16:30.222 --> 16:33.158
<i>It was almost 24-7.</i>

16:33.225 --> 16:35.227
<i>And then--</i>
<i>I'll never forget this</i>

16:35.327 --> 16:37.196
<i>because it was Christmas Day,</i>

16:37.296 --> 16:39.131
and I got a call
early in the morning

16:39.198 --> 16:41.033
from my boss, and he said,

16:41.133 --> 16:42.701
"Go buy flowers

16:42.801 --> 16:46.071
and bring them over
to Brittany's house."

16:46.171 --> 16:48.640
<i>I brought flowers,</i>
<i>buzzed the buzzer.</i>

16:48.707 --> 16:50.976
<i>Simon answered.</i>
<i>So I said, "Merry Christmas.</i>

16:51.043 --> 16:54.013
<i>I'm just so sorry</i>
<i>about Brittany."</i>

16:54.079 --> 16:57.182
I said, "My card's there
if you want to talk,

16:57.249 --> 16:59.218
but no pressure."

16:59.318 --> 17:01.220
<i>And drive off.</i>

17:01.320 --> 17:02.688
<i>It wasn't even an hour later.</i>

17:02.755 --> 17:04.256
<i>Get a call</i>
<i>from an unknown number,</i>

17:04.356 --> 17:06.592
but I answered, and it's Simon.
[chuckles]

17:06.692 --> 17:10.262
And I'm like, "What?"
Like, "Why are you calling me?"

17:10.362 --> 17:12.031
I was kind of, like, shocked.

17:12.097 --> 17:14.199
I said..."Hi."

17:14.266 --> 17:15.734
And he said,
"This is Amber, right?"

17:15.834 --> 17:17.236
And I said, "Yeah."
And he said, "Thank you.

17:17.336 --> 17:18.604
I got your flowers."

17:18.704 --> 17:20.272
And he was kind of silent
for a minute.

17:20.372 --> 17:23.041
He said, "You know, you're
the only one I've called."

17:23.108 --> 17:24.276
And I said, "Oh."

17:24.376 --> 17:26.078
"And I've decided
you're the only one

17:26.178 --> 17:28.013
I want to talk to."

17:28.080 --> 17:30.749
I had access to him now.

17:30.849 --> 17:33.685
<i>[camera shutter clicking]</i>

17:33.752 --> 17:36.455
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:36.555 --> 17:39.091
<i>- Many people in Hollywood</i>
<i>are absolutely shocked</i>

17:39.191 --> 17:40.759
<i>over Murphy's passing.</i>

17:40.859 --> 17:42.928
<i>She began her career</i>
<i>at an extremely young age,</i>

17:43.028 --> 17:46.432
<i>starting with small roles</i>
<i>in commercials and sitcoms.</i>

17:46.532 --> 17:49.868
<i>[audience laughter]</i>

17:51.437 --> 17:54.773
- [laughing goofily]

17:56.375 --> 17:58.777
<i>- Brittany was successful</i>
<i>immediately,</i>

17:58.877 --> 18:00.479
<i>booking pilot after pilot.</i>

18:00.579 --> 18:04.883
<i>I just couldn't believe</i>
<i>how much work this girl got.</i>

18:04.950 --> 18:06.485
My name is Lisa Rieffel,

18:06.585 --> 18:09.221
and I was friends
with Brittany Murphy.

18:09.288 --> 18:11.423
We were both childhood actors.

18:11.490 --> 18:12.991
<i>We both loved singing</i>

18:13.092 --> 18:16.261
and the same boys sometimes.
[chuckles]

18:16.328 --> 18:18.097
And got a lot of jobs together.

18:18.163 --> 18:20.299
So this was from a party

18:20.399 --> 18:23.001
celebrating us
both getting pilots.

18:23.102 --> 18:25.137
- My name is Chris Snyder,
and I'm a manager,

18:25.237 --> 18:27.739
and I was Brittany Murphy's
first agent

18:27.806 --> 18:29.141
in Los Angeles.

18:29.241 --> 18:32.177
<i>Brittany was 14</i>

18:32.277 --> 18:34.613
<i>when she came</i>
<i>into the offices.</i>

18:34.680 --> 18:35.948
<i>TV was fun,</i>

18:36.014 --> 18:38.016
but Brittany wanted
to be a movie star

18:38.117 --> 18:39.985
with every fiber of her being.

18:40.085 --> 18:42.187
She wanted to be in films.

18:42.287 --> 18:45.090
- But, remember, Dorothy,
you're not in Kansas anymore.

18:48.127 --> 18:49.828
<i>- My name's Amy Heckerling.</i>

18:49.928 --> 18:52.131
I'm the writer-director
of "Clueless,"

18:52.197 --> 18:55.033
which was the first movie
that Brittany Murphy was in.

18:55.134 --> 18:58.637
We saw a lot of people
for the part of Tai.

18:58.704 --> 19:02.674
And I felt like everybody
was kind of acting it

19:02.774 --> 19:05.511
as opposed to just feeling it.

19:05.611 --> 19:09.548
And when Brittany came in,
she was just genuine.

19:09.648 --> 19:11.984
She just felt like a sweet girl

19:12.050 --> 19:15.020
who kind of didn't fit in
with the others

19:15.120 --> 19:18.657
and was just trying
and being nice

19:18.724 --> 19:21.727
but, like,
was lost in this world.

19:21.827 --> 19:25.130
And that was exactly
what I was looking for.

19:25.197 --> 19:27.332
<i>- And background.</i>

19:27.399 --> 19:29.067
<i>- When we were shooting</i>
<i>"Clueless,"</i>

19:29.168 --> 19:32.404
<i>Brittany was 17,</i>
<i>so just a kid.</i>

19:32.504 --> 19:35.374
<i>It was a very wonderful</i>
<i>group of people,</i>

19:35.474 --> 19:38.043
<i>and they all started</i>
<i>to have these friendships,</i>

19:38.143 --> 19:40.312
<i>and she was younger</i>
<i>than everybody.</i>

19:40.379 --> 19:43.048
<i>And there was kind of</i>
<i>a sweet, childish,</i>

19:43.148 --> 19:45.184
<i>lost quality that she had</i>

19:45.250 --> 19:47.719
that just breaks your heart.

19:47.819 --> 19:49.188
<i>- When she got that part,</i>

19:49.254 --> 19:51.256
<i>it was like</i>
<i>the "Hallelujah Chorus."</i>

19:51.356 --> 19:54.359
<i>And you're always happy</i>
<i>to give people that news,</i>

19:54.426 --> 19:57.663
because you know it's about
to change their whole life.

19:57.729 --> 20:01.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:07.839 --> 20:09.741
- That's some bump
you got there.

20:09.841 --> 20:10.943
- Yeah.
- Yeah?

20:11.043 --> 20:12.611
You ready to go back
out there?

20:12.711 --> 20:14.580
- Yeah, I am.
- All right.

20:14.680 --> 20:15.747
You sure?
Can you do this?

20:15.847 --> 20:17.783
♪ Rolling
with the homies ♪

20:17.883 --> 20:19.618
- ♪ Rolling
with the homies ♪

20:19.718 --> 20:21.720
- Yeah, let's do it,
you're ready.

20:21.787 --> 20:23.555
- Put it in
the Criterion Collection.

20:23.622 --> 20:25.023
Put it in the Hall of Fame.

20:25.090 --> 20:26.458
This is one of
the greatest movies ever made,

20:26.558 --> 20:28.193
and I'll fight anyone
who disagrees.

20:28.260 --> 20:31.597
You cannot be a teen girl
and not love this movie.

20:31.697 --> 20:34.866
You cannot be a teen girl
and not love Brittany in it.

20:34.933 --> 20:36.268
- Wow.

20:36.368 --> 20:39.271
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

20:39.371 --> 20:42.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:42.608 --> 20:44.710
<i>- She just gets</i>
<i>every cute line,</i>

20:44.776 --> 20:47.079
<i>and she gets</i>
<i>every cute little moment.</i>

20:47.145 --> 20:50.082
- You're a virgin
who can't drive.

20:50.148 --> 20:52.117
<i>- One of the greatest lines</i>
<i>ever written,</i>

20:52.217 --> 20:54.953
<i>one of the greatest line</i>
<i>deliveries ever.</i>

20:55.053 --> 20:56.622
- That was way harsh, Tai.

20:56.722 --> 20:58.757
<i>- "You're a virgin</i>
<i>who can't drive"--</i>

20:58.824 --> 21:02.661
the way she delivers it
just, like, gives you chills.

21:02.761 --> 21:04.496
It's like, whoa.

21:04.596 --> 21:06.431
<i>I loved her performance.</i>

21:06.498 --> 21:09.968
<i>She let her sweetness</i>
<i>shine through.</i>

21:10.068 --> 21:13.505
<i>So you got to see</i>
<i>who she was and love her,</i>

21:13.605 --> 21:15.274
which was important.

21:15.340 --> 21:17.175
<i>- You know, you hear sometimes</i>
<i>about the other girls</i>

21:17.276 --> 21:19.244
<i>that they considered for Cher</i>
<i>in "Clueless."</i>

21:19.311 --> 21:21.280
I've never heard anyone
talk about anyone

21:21.346 --> 21:23.115
who could have played Tai
except for Brittney Murphy.

21:23.181 --> 21:24.650
- [laughs]

21:24.750 --> 21:26.451
<i>- It's the launch</i>
<i>of her career.</i>

21:26.518 --> 21:27.986
And if you don't like
this movie,

21:28.086 --> 21:30.122
you're probably a bad person
with bad taste.

21:30.188 --> 21:32.190
<i>- It wasn't until I saw it,</i>

21:32.291 --> 21:33.659
<i>sitting in the theater,</i>

21:33.759 --> 21:36.261
I felt like,
"She's gonna be a star.

21:36.328 --> 21:38.330
She is gonna be a huge star."

21:38.430 --> 21:40.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:40.332 --> 21:42.334
[reporters shouting]

21:42.434 --> 21:44.436
<i>- Brittany Murphy.</i>

21:49.274 --> 21:50.942
- I don't think
she was in school.

21:51.009 --> 21:52.678
She might've been emancipated.

21:53.845 --> 21:57.816
<i>- She didn't have to go</i>
<i>to school like normal kids.</i>

21:57.883 --> 21:59.351
<i>They gave you the books.</i>

21:59.451 --> 22:01.687
You could not go
for weeks on end

22:01.787 --> 22:03.388
and just turn in
your assignments.

22:03.488 --> 22:07.125
- Most of your learning takes
place on set with a tutor.

22:07.192 --> 22:08.794
When you're working
all the time

22:08.860 --> 22:10.862
and you're not around
kids a lot

22:10.962 --> 22:13.498
and your only friends
are other actors,

22:13.565 --> 22:15.467
you miss a lot of things.

22:15.534 --> 22:17.869
<i>- You don't become as aware</i>

22:17.969 --> 22:20.072
<i>of people and what they can do</i>

22:20.172 --> 22:23.375
<i>and the petty stuff</i>
<i>that people can do or lies--</i>

22:23.475 --> 22:25.210
<i>all that little stuff</i>
<i>that you work out</i>

22:25.310 --> 22:27.346
<i>in junior high</i>
<i>and high school.</i>

22:27.412 --> 22:30.048
So they kind of get caught
into this vacuum

22:30.148 --> 22:31.917
of not knowing who a good
person is

22:32.017 --> 22:33.552
and who a bad person is.

22:33.652 --> 22:36.588
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:36.688 --> 22:43.562
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:43.662 --> 22:45.163
- How are you coping?

22:45.230 --> 22:46.331
- You don't really cope.

22:46.398 --> 22:48.033
You just kind of...

22:48.100 --> 22:49.401
live this surreal life

22:49.501 --> 22:52.437
and hope that one day
it makes sense.

22:52.537 --> 22:54.039
I'm gonna go home.
- All right.

22:54.106 --> 22:56.174
Thank you very much.
Thank you.

22:56.241 --> 23:00.545
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:02.514 --> 23:04.416
<i>- I'm Roger Neal,</i>
<i>the publicist</i>

23:04.516 --> 23:06.184
<i>for Simon Monjack</i>
<i>and Sharon Murphy,</i>

23:06.251 --> 23:07.686
<i>post-Brittany's death.</i>

23:07.753 --> 23:10.389
So, about a month after
Brittany passed away,

23:10.455 --> 23:13.291
I received a phone call
from Simon Monjack.

23:13.392 --> 23:14.893
They needed a publicist
'cause there was

23:14.960 --> 23:16.928
a lot going on in the press,
a lot of rumors.

23:17.028 --> 23:19.965
When I got the call to go meet
with Simon and Sharon,

23:20.065 --> 23:23.101
I went on the Internet
and did a search.

23:23.201 --> 23:24.703
So this shot here--

23:24.770 --> 23:26.438
I wouldn't have them put
in that position.

23:26.538 --> 23:29.541
To me, that's not a typical
son-in-law-mother-in-law pose

23:29.608 --> 23:31.042
for a photo.

23:31.109 --> 23:34.146
We're talking
about tabloid-media fodder.

23:34.246 --> 23:36.448
<i>They had done some interviews</i>

23:36.548 --> 23:38.717
<i>because "Larry King"</i>
<i>is the one interview</i>

23:38.784 --> 23:40.385
<i>that the world watches.</i>

23:40.452 --> 23:42.721
But watching that show,
man, they--

23:42.788 --> 23:44.656
Mm-mm.
It wasn't good for them at all.

23:44.756 --> 23:46.792
- You didn't want
an autopsy at first?

23:46.892 --> 23:48.160
- No, I didn't.

23:48.260 --> 23:51.296
There was this woman
who just lost a daughter.

23:51.396 --> 23:52.664
It was such a shock.

23:52.764 --> 23:54.099
This pristine body

23:54.166 --> 23:55.667
that is curvy
in all the right places...

23:55.767 --> 23:57.302
- It's not like
she was in a car accident.

23:57.402 --> 23:59.004
- And with skin like silk.

23:59.104 --> 24:01.640
And how could I say in front
of her mother, "Cut her up"?

24:01.740 --> 24:04.409
- When I watch it,
I sort of, like--

24:04.476 --> 24:05.777
It's like, "Oh, no."

24:05.844 --> 24:09.147
It made you cringe
watching some of it,

24:09.247 --> 24:11.116
and she seemed
a little out of it.

24:11.183 --> 24:12.617
- You were living in the house?

24:12.684 --> 24:13.985
- Sharon lived with us
throughout the marriage.

24:14.085 --> 24:15.454
- Yeah, I was--
- The three of you

24:15.520 --> 24:17.122
lived together?
- I was always there.

24:17.189 --> 24:19.291
And my daughter and I lived
together always.

24:19.357 --> 24:21.126
- So what happened that day?
- It was the three of us.

24:21.193 --> 24:23.361
- That's why these rumors
are so ludicrous.

24:23.462 --> 24:25.797
<i>- I actually saw part of it.</i>

24:25.864 --> 24:27.699
I had that question in my mind,

24:27.799 --> 24:31.002
"Is this for real
or is this bull?"

24:31.102 --> 24:33.505
<i>I was contacted by the driver</i>

24:33.605 --> 24:35.140
<i>that was driving them</i>
<i>that night,</i>

24:35.207 --> 24:37.676
<i>who happened to be</i>
<i>an LAPD officer</i>

24:37.776 --> 24:40.178
<i>who moonlighted</i>
<i>as a chauffeur.</i>

24:40.278 --> 24:42.147
<i>And he said,</i>
<i>"They got to the studio.</i>

24:42.214 --> 24:44.616
<i>"They did this</i>
<i>very tearful interview</i>

24:44.683 --> 24:46.284
<i>in front of Larry King."</i>

24:46.351 --> 24:48.987
- Larry, we have clung
to each other.

24:49.054 --> 24:50.188
- It's been weeks.

24:50.288 --> 24:53.191
- We cry day after day
after day.

24:53.291 --> 24:55.393
I lay, and I look
at the ceiling.

24:55.494 --> 24:59.364
My mother-in-law comes in
with neuropathy, shaking,

24:59.464 --> 25:01.500
