- See what I mean?

36:39.730 --> 36:41.165
- So I hear
you're a dope rapper.

36:41.232 --> 36:43.067
- That could be the other--
- I like that.

36:43.167 --> 36:46.504
- So I hear you're
a real dope rapper.

36:46.571 --> 36:47.905
<i>- So she was nervous.</i>

36:48.005 --> 36:49.740
<i>I mean, that was</i>
<i>a big role for her,</i>

36:49.840 --> 36:51.709
<i>working across a huge artist.</i>

36:51.776 --> 36:53.911
It can start
to put pressure on you,

36:54.011 --> 36:56.247
to where you
might just even fold.

36:56.347 --> 36:57.848
<i>I really liked</i>
<i>the first time, like,</i>

36:57.915 --> 36:59.350
<i>they make out</i>
<i>in, like, the factory.</i>

36:59.417 --> 37:01.552
<i>Like, she went,</i>
<i>like, all the way.</i>

37:01.619 --> 37:03.221
<i>She just had a lot of courage.</i>

37:03.287 --> 37:05.856
<i>On "action," like,</i>
<i>any type of inhibitions</i>

37:05.923 --> 37:07.225
<i>just went away.</i>

37:07.291 --> 37:09.427
<i>- Was there romance</i>
<i>off the screen?</i>

37:09.527 --> 37:11.929
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, sure.
- How did that go?

37:12.029 --> 37:13.231
- Well, it went.

37:13.297 --> 37:15.766
It came and went.
[laughs]

37:15.866 --> 37:17.702
- It's fascinating
to know that

37:17.768 --> 37:21.439
the onscreen chemistry also
is going off the screen.

37:21.539 --> 37:23.708
And, look, I might've been
a little jealous at that one.

37:23.774 --> 37:25.109
Like, "Is it--damn it!"

37:25.209 --> 37:27.111
You know, like,
Marshall's awesome, but--

37:27.211 --> 37:30.381
No, I'm joking,
but it was speculated.

37:30.448 --> 37:33.451
<i>After "8 Mile"</i>
<i>she became the it girl</i>

37:33.551 --> 37:34.752
<i>and I was thinking,</i>

37:34.819 --> 37:36.954
"This is what dreams
are made of."

37:37.054 --> 37:38.756
Like, she was up there.

37:38.823 --> 37:41.959
[crowd cheering]

37:43.561 --> 37:45.296
- You're gonna be great.

37:45.396 --> 37:48.065
<i>[spacey music]</i>

37:48.132 --> 37:50.635
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:55.139 --> 37:57.441
<i>[bell tolls]</i>

37:57.508 --> 38:00.845
- Welcome to my house.

38:00.945 --> 38:04.315
Now, to get into the house...

38:04.415 --> 38:07.418
you have to put
your thumb here.

38:07.485 --> 38:10.755
[device beeps]
And then...

38:10.821 --> 38:12.690
it opens.

38:12.790 --> 38:15.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:15.192 --> 38:17.128
<i>- He actually said,</i>

38:17.194 --> 38:18.863
<i>"Do you want to come</i>
<i>to the house?"</i>

38:18.963 --> 38:21.332
I'm like, "Yeah, like, yeah."

38:21.432 --> 38:24.835
And he even said, you know,
"You'd have first access."

38:24.935 --> 38:27.638
<i>It was amazing,</i>
<i>but it felt weird</i>

38:27.705 --> 38:29.974
<i>for this grieving husband</i>
<i>to be like,</i>

38:30.041 --> 38:32.443
<i>"Let's show the world</i>
<i>where Brittany died."</i>

38:32.510 --> 38:34.111
- Yeah, these are pictures
I took of Brittany.

38:34.178 --> 38:36.614
This was actually used
at the funeral.

38:36.681 --> 38:40.184
just thought it was
a perfect theatrical photograph

38:40.284 --> 38:44.989
of someone who is just taking
their final bow.

38:45.056 --> 38:47.792
<i>- Their house--</i>
<i>it was so much security</i>

38:47.858 --> 38:51.329
<i>that you're like,</i>
<i>"Whoa, wait, why?"</i>

38:51.395 --> 38:54.699
<i>He sort of alluded to, like,</i>
<i>"We've been targeted,"</i>

38:54.799 --> 38:57.568
<i>almost like</i>
<i>a conspiracy theorist would.</i>

38:57.668 --> 39:02.540
Like, people in the government
were watching them.

39:02.640 --> 39:06.344
- Lots of Louis Vuitton
and lots of Chanel, Gucci.

39:06.410 --> 39:07.845
Actually, that's a really nice
leather jacket.

39:07.912 --> 39:09.714
I never saw her wear that.

39:09.814 --> 39:10.815
Isn't that cute?

39:10.881 --> 39:14.251
But there's just so much of it.

39:14.352 --> 39:15.986
<i>- I was a little bit surprised</i>

39:16.053 --> 39:18.322
<i>because it wasn't</i>
<i>what I was expecting.</i>

39:18.389 --> 39:20.991
<i>When you think of Hollywood</i>
<i>and people with lots of money,</i>

39:21.058 --> 39:24.228
<i>you think of like</i>
<i>a big, clean, modern house.</i>

39:24.328 --> 39:26.897
<i>Eventually we went</i>
<i>up to the master bedroom,</i>

39:26.997 --> 39:30.401
<i>which had the bathroom</i>
<i>where she was found.</i>

39:30.501 --> 39:33.070
- This is obviously
the infamous bathroom,

39:33.170 --> 39:37.074
which no one has managed to
even come in and clean out yet.

39:37.174 --> 39:40.244
This is the little doggy couch

39:40.344 --> 39:41.779
where she actually fell.

39:41.879 --> 39:44.014
She fell
on Clara's chaise longue.

39:44.081 --> 39:46.016
She was put
on her side right here

39:46.083 --> 39:47.752
next to the chaise lounge.

39:47.852 --> 39:49.720
And then when
the paramedics came in,

39:49.787 --> 39:53.557
they pulled her through here
into the...

39:55.025 --> 39:59.029
Into--through the--
one of the closets

39:59.096 --> 40:01.632
into the main room, so...

40:01.732 --> 40:03.968
Yeah, you're the first people
to ever see

40:04.068 --> 40:05.603
the infamous bathroom.

40:05.703 --> 40:08.105
And it's the first time
I've come in here, actually.

40:08.205 --> 40:09.607
- You don't use
this bathroom anymore?

40:09.707 --> 40:11.308
- No, no,
I don't use it at all.

40:11.409 --> 40:14.412
[stammering]
Yeah, it's shocking.

40:14.478 --> 40:17.248
<i>[dark music]</i>

40:17.314 --> 40:20.117
<i>- It was the first time</i>
<i>I met Sharon.</i>

40:20.217 --> 40:22.486
She acted like
he was in control.

40:22.586 --> 40:25.556
Like, she acted submissive
with him,

40:25.623 --> 40:27.391
which I noticed,

40:27.458 --> 40:29.293
and it struck a chord.

40:29.393 --> 40:31.128
What happens
when no one's here?

40:31.228 --> 40:33.063
Or--or how do they act,

40:33.130 --> 40:34.465
you know, when no one's here?

40:34.565 --> 40:36.567
Because I remember
going into the house,

40:36.634 --> 40:40.404
and the master bedroom bed
was all ruffled,

40:40.471 --> 40:42.173
a mess, like, both sides.

40:42.273 --> 40:45.910
And I was like, "Well, that's
weird because Brittany's gone."

40:45.976 --> 40:48.479
And it just--like, in a way
that you could tell

40:48.579 --> 40:51.615
two people had been
in that bed, recently.

40:51.682 --> 40:53.250
And I said something to him.

40:53.317 --> 40:54.652
And he said,
"Oh, well, Sharon and I--

40:54.752 --> 40:56.353
"Sharon crawls in
with me sometimes,

40:56.454 --> 40:58.322
and we just cry."

40:58.422 --> 41:00.691
And you're like,
"That's weird."

41:00.791 --> 41:03.294
Like, it is weird.

41:03.360 --> 41:05.196
<i>- She's told the coroner</i>

41:05.296 --> 41:09.099
that her and Simon
have been sharing a bed

41:09.166 --> 41:14.004
<i>to comfort each other</i>
<i>after the death of Brittany.</i>

41:14.104 --> 41:15.706
Oh, hell, no.

41:15.806 --> 41:17.975
That is so gro--

41:18.042 --> 41:20.344
like, it's so creepy
and so gross.

41:20.444 --> 41:23.147
<i>- I encountered a woman</i>
<i>who was scared,</i>

41:23.214 --> 41:26.116
<i>who was distraught,</i>
<i>who was heartbroken,</i>

41:26.183 --> 41:30.054
<i>who had not really grieved</i>
<i>her daughter.</i>

41:30.154 --> 41:32.022
<i>But it was absurd,</i>

41:32.122 --> 41:36.494
completely absurd to even think
that Sharon and her son-in-law

41:36.560 --> 41:39.029
<i>were anything but</i>
<i>mother-in-law and son-in-law.</i>

41:39.129 --> 41:40.731
<i>She loved him like a son.</i>

41:40.831 --> 41:43.367
<i>There was nothing like</i>
<i>what had been speculated.</i>

41:43.467 --> 41:46.303
- Another thing
that was strange

41:46.370 --> 41:50.474
was Brittany left everything
in her will to her mother.

41:50.541 --> 41:53.477
- You were the beneficiary
of the entire state.

41:53.544 --> 41:55.179
Was it a sizable estate?

41:55.246 --> 41:57.214
- We haven't even begun
to add it up.

41:57.314 --> 41:59.016
- I have no idea.
I really don't--

41:59.083 --> 42:01.485
- I'm just asking.
- And I'm just telling you--

42:01.552 --> 42:03.187
we're not doing math.

42:03.254 --> 42:06.023
We're eating, we're living,
I'm paying the bills.

42:06.090 --> 42:08.492
They haven't even looked
at Brittany's estate yet.

42:08.559 --> 42:10.160
- He didn't have
any work going,

42:10.227 --> 42:12.062
and he wasn't producing
anything or writing anything.

42:12.162 --> 42:13.898
But now he's kind of
in a financial position

42:13.998 --> 42:16.333
where he doesn't have control
over any of her money.

42:16.400 --> 42:17.701
Sharon has all the money.

42:17.768 --> 42:19.737
<i>- His job was Brittany Murphy,</i>

42:19.837 --> 42:24.008
so he had to think of ways
to make money.

42:24.074 --> 42:25.376
- Where do you two
go from here?

42:25.442 --> 42:28.345
You go back East?
- I'm going where--

42:28.412 --> 42:30.948
[both laugh]

42:31.048 --> 42:32.783
We're glued.
We need each other.

42:32.883 --> 42:34.251
- We have a job to do.

42:34.351 --> 42:36.587
It's called
the Brittany Murphy Foundation.

42:36.687 --> 42:41.058
For young people,
for education,

42:41.125 --> 42:43.193
for things like
what's going on in Haiti.

42:43.260 --> 42:45.696
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:45.763 --> 42:47.798
<i>- In the weeks after she died,</i>

42:47.898 --> 42:49.567
I couldn't process it.

42:49.633 --> 42:53.270
So, within a few days,
I think either I reached out

42:53.370 --> 42:55.039
to the family
or they reached out to--

42:55.105 --> 42:57.274
I forget which,
'cause it was a kind of a blur.

42:57.374 --> 43:00.778
But I remember I said,
"Let me put together

43:00.878 --> 43:03.280
a compilation video,
like a memorial video."

43:03.380 --> 43:05.082
[indistinct chatter]

43:05.149 --> 43:06.917
<i>I remember I was</i>
<i>in the middle of editing</i>

43:06.984 --> 43:08.319
<i>this memorial video,</i>

43:08.419 --> 43:10.254
<i>email arrived</i>
<i>with an invitation,</i>

43:10.321 --> 43:11.956
and it talked
about a contribution

43:12.056 --> 43:13.557
to the Brittany Murphy
Foundation--

43:13.624 --> 43:15.626
a cash amount
that was requested

43:15.726 --> 43:17.628
of several thousand dollars
or something,

43:17.728 --> 43:22.399
and I kept thinking,
"Why would you do that?"

43:22.466 --> 43:25.469
<i>- Simon comes out</i>
<i>and tells the world</i>

43:25.569 --> 43:27.471
that he started a foundation
and that he is going to

43:27.571 --> 43:29.907
charge friends and family
to come to this memorial.

43:29.974 --> 43:34.078
<i>It was just viewed as tacky</i>
<i>and money-grubbing.</i>

43:34.144 --> 43:36.647
- I remember having a really
negative reaction to it.

43:36.747 --> 43:39.650
And I called a few people,
and they agreed.

43:39.750 --> 43:41.752
I think within, like,
literally, within hours,

43:41.819 --> 43:43.754
<i>some of the press</i>
<i>had picked up on it,</i>

43:43.821 --> 43:45.522
<i>and there was major pushback.</i>

43:45.623 --> 43:47.358
<i>And not a surprise,</i>
<i>within a few days,</i>

43:47.458 --> 43:50.327
the whole thing evaporated,
and there never was a memorial.

43:50.427 --> 43:53.130
- The world could see
that this man was now trying

43:53.197 --> 43:54.765
to profit off
of his wife's death

43:54.832 --> 43:57.267
<i>in a really bizarre way.</i>

43:57.334 --> 44:00.371
- He was just kind of,
like, a scammy guy.

44:00.471 --> 44:02.172
He was a little scammer.

44:02.272 --> 44:05.542
<i>- You go from Ashton Kutcher</i>
<i>to Simon Monjack,</i>

44:05.643 --> 44:06.710
<i>and there's some--</i>

44:06.810 --> 44:08.278
there's some questions there.

44:08.345 --> 44:11.548
[camera shutters clicking,
reporters clamoring]

44:15.786 --> 44:18.222
<i>- We both liked the same boy</i>
<i>at one point.</i>

44:18.322 --> 44:19.823
She got him, though.

44:19.890 --> 44:21.225
- [laughs]
- Thanks.

44:21.325 --> 44:22.893
- There was some
flirtation going on,

44:22.993 --> 44:24.695
and then I showed up
to some party,

44:24.795 --> 44:27.998
and he's like, "Yeah, that's
my new girlfriend, Brittany."

44:28.065 --> 44:30.567
[laughs]
It's like, "Oh, cool."

44:30.668 --> 44:32.870
[screaming]

44:32.970 --> 44:34.672
<i>- At the time, for women,</i>

44:34.738 --> 44:37.074
<i>that was not</i>
<i>a lot of opportunities.</i>

44:37.174 --> 44:38.909
<i>There could be rom-coms</i>

44:39.009 --> 44:41.812
<i>focused on a female audience</i>
<i>of, like,</i>

44:41.879 --> 44:45.249
some amazing romance
that has some funny stuff

44:45.349 --> 44:47.151
and weird beginnings
or whatever.

44:47.217 --> 44:48.919
I don't know
what the pattern is.

44:49.019 --> 44:52.356
<i>They were trying to stick her</i>
<i>into that for a while.</i>

44:52.423 --> 44:55.059
<i>And, you know,</i>
<i>her and Ashton seemed cute.</i>

44:55.159 --> 44:57.194
- Ashton and Brittany,

44:57.261 --> 44:59.596
from pretty early on,

44:59.697 --> 45:01.331
even before they were
romantically linked,

45:01.398 --> 45:04.068
there was just
a chemistry to them,

45:04.168 --> 45:06.537
<i>comedically, physically,</i>
<i>and on-screen.</i>

45:06.603 --> 45:08.939
And the fact that
that carried off-screen

45:09.039 --> 45:10.574
fed into a narrative

45:10.674 --> 45:12.743
that certainly didn't hurt
the movie.

45:12.843 --> 45:14.545
[reporters clamoring]

45:14.611 --> 45:16.880
<i>- In a way, "Just Married"</i>
<i>is the height</i>

45:16.947 --> 45:18.782
<i>of her as a movie star.</i>

45:18.882 --> 45:21.185
It makes
just over $100 million,

45:21.251 --> 45:22.753
and she is dating
Ashton Kutcher

45:22.853 --> 45:24.621
at the time
that they're promoting it.

45:24.722 --> 45:27.024
<i>That's her being an it girl.</i>

45:27.091 --> 45:29.860
<i>- Star of "Just Married."</i>
<i>- With Brittany Murphy.</i>

45:29.927 --> 45:31.261
<i>- Which is</i>
<i>your new girlfriend.</i>

45:31.361 --> 45:33.230
<i>She got to be big</i>
<i>from "Clueless,"</i>

45:33.297 --> 45:35.132
<i>but can you believe she was</i>
<i>the ugly chick in "Clueless"?</i>

45:35.232 --> 45:36.600
<i>But she was a fat, ugly chick.</i>

45:36.700 --> 45:38.602
<i>She tried</i>
<i>to transform herself.</i>

45:38.702 --> 45:40.437
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

45:40.537 --> 45:42.272
<i>I don't mean to be hard on</i>
<i>your girlfriend, but she seems</i>

45:42.372 --> 45:43.807
<i>like she's been around the</i>
<i>block a couple of times.</i>

45:43.907 --> 45:45.442
<i>- You know what?</i>
<i>I think she's had, like,</i>

45:45.542 --> 45:47.211
<i>three boyfriends ever.</i>
<i>- Oh, really?</i>

45:47.277 --> 45:49.113
<i>You better wear a condom.</i>
<i>She's been with Eminem.</i>

45:49.213 --> 45:51.248
<i>- Oh, stop it.</i>
<i>What are you saying?</i>

45:51.315 --> 45:52.816
<i>- I'm just saying, who knows</i>
<i>what he's been up to?</i>

45:52.916 --> 45:54.451
<i>When you saw</i>
<i>the movie "Clueless,"</i>

45:54.551 --> 45:56.120
<i>did you ever think</i>
<i>you'd be banging her?</i>

45:56.220 --> 45:57.654
<i>- Yeah, but you know</i>
<i>what they always do</i>

45:57.755 --> 45:59.156
<i>with the ugly girl</i>
<i>in the movie?</i>

45:59.256 --> 46:00.724
<i>It's always, like,</i>
<i>a pretty girl</i>

46:00.791 --> 46:02.593
<i>that they, like, do down.</i>
- It's true.

46:02.659 --> 46:04.561
<i>- But she was</i>
<i>a fat, ugly chick.</i>

46:04.628 --> 46:06.597
- She wasn't fat. Howard--

46:06.663 --> 46:08.665
<i>- What are you talking about?</i>

46:08.766 --> 46:10.300
<i>- Those people are complicit.</i>

46:10.400 --> 46:11.802
All of the people
who wrote about her

46:11.902 --> 46:13.904
and talked about her
and made the headline

46:13.971 --> 46:16.306
about this gorgeous--

46:16.406 --> 46:19.910
she wasn't even, like,
in society's terms, fat.

46:19.977 --> 46:21.478
She was, like, perfectly sized.

46:21.578 --> 46:24.648
And then she goes, "Okay,"
and loses the weight,

46:24.748 --> 46:27.117
and we're not sure
if it was healthy or not

46:27.184 --> 46:28.819
and then still after her.

46:28.919 --> 46:30.521
It's like, leave women alone.

46:30.621 --> 46:33.290
Let her do her damn job.
We don't do this to men.

46:33.357 --> 46:35.759
[indistinct shouting]

46:35.826 --> 46:38.262
<i>- I read everything</i>
<i>that is written about me.</i>

46:38.328 --> 46:41.665
<i>"All the bad things that are</i>
<i>said and all the bad reports.</i>

46:41.765 --> 46:45.002
<i>"I am not and never have been</i>
<i>anorexic or bulimic.</i>

46:45.102 --> 46:47.371
<i>"Also, Ashton</i>
<i>didn't break up with me.</i>

46:47.471 --> 46:49.540
<i>It was mutual."</i>
<i>- There's a price to pay</i>

46:49.640 --> 46:51.175
<i>for being a celebrity,</i>
<i>for sure.</i>

46:51.275 --> 46:53.010
<i>I mean, if you start out</i>
<i>wanting to be an artist</i>

46:53.110 --> 46:54.611
and then you find out
you're a celebrity,

46:54.678 --> 46:56.180
it's not always what you think
it's gonna be.

46:56.280 --> 46:57.648
It can take a toll
on everything.

46:57.714 --> 46:59.550
<i>It can take a toll</i>
<i>on your health</i>

46:59.650 --> 47:01.852
<i>and on your relationships.</i>

47:01.952 --> 47:03.987
<i>- Do you remember when</i>
<i>she broke up with Ashton?</i>

47:04.054 --> 47:05.556
- Mm-hmm.
- Them dating?

47:05.656 --> 47:06.723
- Mm-hmm.

47:06.824 --> 47:08.358
I don't want
to talk about that.

47:08.458 --> 47:10.027
Who cares?
Just a breakup.

47:10.127 --> 47:13.197
- I know that there
were situations

47:13.297 --> 47:14.965
that left her heartbroken.

47:15.032 --> 47:18.569
<i>She must have been, like,</i>
<i>searching for something</i>

47:18.669 --> 47:22.139
<i>that wasn't coming through</i>
<i>or wasn't being realistic</i>

47:22.206 --> 47:25.042
<i>in the sort of</i>
<i>Hollywood universe.</i>

47:25.142 --> 47:32.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:34.852 --> 47:37.855
<i>- I think as human beings,</i>
<i>we second-guess ourselves,</i>

47:37.921 --> 47:41.992
and we wonder, and we also
get used to habits and--

47:42.059 --> 47:43.427
<i>and depending</i>
<i>on certain people</i>

47:43.527 --> 47:44.761
that may be unhealthy
for your life.

47:44.862 --> 47:46.263
And you don't realize it
at the time,

47:46.363 --> 47:47.698
but once you're free of them,
then you realize

47:47.764 --> 47:49.199
there's a whole universe
out there,

47:49.266 --> 47:51.235
and you feel like
